HEADWORD: Evaporometer
<hw>E*vap`o*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>evaporare</ets> to evaporate + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧vaporm⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>An instrument for ascertaining the quantity of a fluid evaporated
in a given time; an atmometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

